{"serial": "43019", "department_serial": 41, "code": "IM4001", "class": "E", "name": {"en": "Information Systems Development Project Ⅱ", "ch": "資訊系統發展專題Ⅱ"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Chen, Chung-Yang"], "ch": ["陳仲儼"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 6, "session": ["6", "7", "8"]}, "loc": {"building": "I1", "room": "105"}}], "isRequired": true, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": -1, "department": {"ch": "資訊管理學系", "en": "Department of Information Management"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "不使用", "en": "None"}, "assigned": 0, "selected": 15, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "藉由專題製作，讓同學將要製作的專題置入企業組織與運作中去了解其問題與需求，並學習思考如何透過資訊科技來加以改善或解決，過程中將整合過去所學的企管知識，系統分析與設計、程式語言、資料庫等知識，並學習以團隊合作的方式來完成。", "en": "“The aim of this course is to provide students the opportunity to apply a range of knowledge and skills developed in the Bachelor of Business Administration (BBA) degree program to the analysis, design and development of a real-world information system project. The course provides an experiential learning environment in which students can practice and integrate knowledge and skills obtained in the BBA degree, and understand real-world business needs and issues. It also enables students to work effectively as a member of a small team and interact with clients.“"}, "outline": {"ch": "本課程教學內容主要著重在指導學生運用敏捷發展法、特別是Scrum來完成系統的開發。", "en": "The teaching of this course mainly includes guiding students to carry out system development using an agile method such as Scrum."}, "textbook": {"ch": "to be updated", "en": "“Chen, Chung-Yang, and P. Pete Chong. ““Software engineering education: A study on conducting collaborative senior project development.““ Journal of systems and Software 84.3 (2011): 479-491.“"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "80", "en": "80"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "研討\n實習/實驗\n個別指導", "en": ["Seminar", "Practical Training Lab", "Individual Inst